  "Broker Comment" : "OTHER RELATED ITEM 22F1; REQ'D AMENDED PAGE 3 FROM NEUBERGER AND BERMAN, DISCLOSES A COMPLAINT AND DECISION ACCEPTING OFFER OF SETTLEMENT BEFORE THE COMMITTEE OF BUSINESS CONDUCT OF THE PHILADELPHIA STOCK EXCHANGE INC., IN THE MATTER OF TMR SECURITIES INC., JAMES H. ELLIS AND IRWIN LAINOFF; THE COMPLAINT ALLEGED: (1) TMR SECURITIES INC., ACTING THROUGH ITS PRESIDENT, JAMES H. ELLIS, AND ITS SECRETARY, IRWIN LAINOFF, FAILED TO PROPERLY REPORT TO STOCK CLEARING CORPORATION OF PHILADELPHIA AN ERROR IN A CONFIRMATION IN THAT ON 1/29/76, A CONFIRMATION ON A TRANSACTION INVOLVING THE SALE OF 5000 SHARES OF INLAND STEEL CO., WAS TRANSMITTED TO TMR SECURITIES INC., WHICH CONFIRMATION WAS NOT PROMPTLY REPORTED TO STOCK CLEARING CORPORATION OF PHILADELPHIA AS BEING AN ERROR. THE ACTS, PRACTICES AND CONDUCT AFORESAID CONSTITUTE SEPARATE AND DISTINCT VIOLATIONS OF RULE 252 OF THE EXCHANGE BY RESPONDENTS, TMR SECURITIES, INC., JAMES H. ELLIS AND IRWIN H. LAINOFF. ** (2) THE AFOREMENTIONED RESPONDENTS MADE MISSTATEMENTS UPON A MATERIAL POINT TO THE COMMITTEE ON BUSINESS CONDUCT AND THE CHIEF EXAMINER OF THE EXCHANGE WHILE HE WAS ACTING ON BEHALF OF THE COMMITTEE ON BUSINESS CONDUCT IN THAT ON MARCH 8, 1976, THE CHIEF EXAMINER WROTE TO JAMES H. ELLIS AND REQUESTED INFORMATION CONCERNING THE TRANSACTION DESCRIBED ABOVE. BY LETTER DATED 3/12/76, IRWIN LAINOFF RESPONDED TO THE REQUEST OF THE CHIEF EXAMINER AND, IN SO DOING, MADE MISSTATEMENTS UPON A MATERIAL POINT. THE ACTS, PRACTICES AND CONDUCT AFORESAID CONSTITUTE SEPARATE AND DISTINCT MISSTATEMENTS UPON A MATERAIL POINT TO A STANDING COMMITTEE AS PROHIBITED BY ARTICLE XVIII: SECTION 18-6 OF THE BY-LAWS OF THE EXCHANGE BY RESPONDENTS. ** (3) THE AFOREMENTIONED RESPONDENTS ENGAGED IN A COURSE OF CONDUCT WHICH WAS INCONSISTENT WITH JUST AND EQUITABLE PRINCIPLES OF TRADE. THE ACTS AND PRACTICES AFORESAID CONSTITUTE SEPARATE AND DISTINCT ACTS OF CONDUCT INCONSISTENT WITH JUST AND EQUITABLE PR*SEE FAQ #1*"
